# For Q5 SDM on circular plasmid with an insertion:
# Forward primer: 5'-[insertion]-[anneals at position 215 onwards]-3'
# Reverse primer: 5'-[revcomp of insertion]-[anneals upstream of position 215, going backwards]-3'
#
# The forward primer annealing region starts at position 215 in the input
# The reverse primer anneals to positions just before 215 (on the opposite strand)
#
# Since it's circular, the reverse primer anneals at some position upstream of 215
# and extends backwards. The forward primer extends forward from 215.

# Strategy: 
# Forward primer = insertion + sequence from input[215..215+len-1]
# Reverse primer = revcomp(insertion) + revcomp(sequence from input[pos..pos+len-1])
# where pos is upstream of 215

